csFeedbackButtonText\"> Feedback</span></span></div></div><div class=\"zDocsTopicActionsMobile\"><button aria-label=\"Show topic actions\" data-toggle=\"dropdown\" id=\"zDocsTopicActionsMobile\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-ellipsis-h\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-ellipsis-h\"></use></svg></button><div class=\"dropdown-menu zDocsDropdownMenu zDocsTopicActionsMobileDropdown dropdown-menu-right\"></div></div><div style=\"flex-basis: 100%; height: 0px;\"></div><ul class=\"zDocsTopicPageDetails\"><li class=\"zDocsTopicPageDate css-cinqea\">Last Updated<span class=\"css-cinqea\">Dez 30, 2022</span></li><li class=\"zDocsAiTopicSummaryDetailsItem\"><button class=\"zDocsAiTopicSummaryButton\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-topic-summary\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-topic-summary\"></use></svg>Summarize</button></li><li class=\"spacer\" role=\"presentation\"></li><div class=\"zDocsLabelWrapper\"><ul><li class=\"zDocsLabel\"><a aria-describedby=\"hyperLinkFacetsTooltip\" class=\"css-ettsdk\" data-tooltip-content=\"Search all site by tag: Uniface\" data-tooltip-id=\"hyperLinkFacetsTooltip\" href=\"/de-DE/search?labelkey=prod_uniface\" stylesprops=\"[object Object]\"><svg aria-label=\"Tag\" class=\"ico-tag\" role=\"img\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-tag\"></use></svg>Uniface</a></li><li class=\"zDocsLabel\"><a aria-describedby=\"hyperLinkFacetsTooltip\" class=\"css-ettsdk\" data-tooltip-content=\"Search all site by tag: 10.4\" data-tooltip-id=\"hyperLinkFacetsTooltip\" href=\"/de-DE/search?labelkey=uniface_10.4\" stylesprops=\"[object Object]\"><svg aria-label=\"Tag\" class=\"ico-tag\" role=\"img\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-tag\"></use></svg>10.4</a></li></ul></div></ul></header><div class=\"zDocsTopicPageBody\" data-prismjs-copy=\"Copy\" data-prismjs-copy-error=\"Copy failed! Use Ctrl + C instead.\" data-prismjs-copy-success=\"Copied!\"><div class=\"zDocsTopicPageBodyContent\" dir=\"ltr\"><div id=\"zDocsAiSummaryContaineruniface_104gzg1665703134326.html\"></div><div><article class=\"hascomments\" data-page=\"bundle:uniface_104/enus/gzg1665703134326.html\" id=\"bundle:uniface_104/enus/gzg1665703134326.html\"><main role=\"main\"><article aria-labelledby=\"ariaid-title1\" class=\"dita\" id=\"gzg1665703134326\" role=\"article\">\n<div class=\"body conbody\" id=\"gzg1665703134326__uggetc_404306\"><p class=\"shortdesc\">Move additional data from the current occurrence of the specified entity or current entity into a program buffer.\n </p>\n<section class=\"section refsyn\" id=\"gzg1665703134326__topic_d121049e1_d121050e1_d121051e1\">\n<div class=\"p\">\n<div class=\"zDocsCodeExplanationContainer\"><button aria-label=\"Explain this code\" class=\"zDocsAiActionsButton\" data-target=\"#zDocsCodeExplanationModal_uniface_104gzg1665703134326_html_0\" data-toggle=\"modal\" tabindex=\"0\" type=\"button\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-code-explanation\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-code-explanation\"></use></svg>Explain this code</button></div><div class=\"code-toolbar\"><pre class=\"pre codeblock language-plaintext\" data-explanation-rendered=\"true\" id=\"gzg1665703134326__codeblock_ihl_mt1_1wb\" tabindex=\"0\"><code class=\"language-plaintext\">short uggetc (unsigned char* entity, unsigned char* buffer, short max);</code></pre><div class=\"toolbar\"><div class=\"toolbar-item\"><button class=\"copy-to-clipboard-button\" data-copy-state=\"copy\" type=\"button\"><span>Copy</span></button></div></div></div>\n</div>\n</section>\n<section class=\"section\" id=\"gzg1665703134326__topic_d85972e1_d85973e1_d85974e1_d85975e1_d85976e1\"><h2 class=\"title sectiontitle\" id=\"d303651e61\">Parameters</h2>\n<dl class=\"dl parml\" id=\"gzg1665703134326__parml_snf_nt1_1wb\">\n<dt class=\"dt pt dlterm\"><var class=\"keyword varname\">entity</var></dt>\n<dd class=\"dd pd\">The name of the entity whose data you want to get. A value of NULL denotes the\n                  current entity.</dd>\n<dt class=\"dt pt dlterm\"><var class=\"keyword varname\">buffer</var></dt>\n<dd class=\"dd pd\">(Output) The buffer containing the data.</dd>\n<dt class=\"dt pt dlterm\"><var class=\"keyword varname\">max</var></dt>\n<dd class=\"dd pd\">The maximum number of bytes that should be moved. This should not exceed the size\n                  of the buffer.</dd>\n</dl>\n</section>\n<section class=\"section\" id=\"gzg1665703134326__topic_d85977e1_d85978e1_d85979e1_d85980e1_d85981e1\"><h2 class=\"title sectiontitle\" id=\"d303651e100\">Return Values</h2>\n<div class=\"table-wrap\"><table class=\"table\" count-columns=\"2\" id=\"gzg1665703134326__d6308e20\"><caption><span class=\"table--title-label\">Table 1. </span><span class=\"title\">Values returned by ugget and uggetc</span></caption><colgroup><col/><col/></colgroup><thead class=\"thead\">\n<tr class=\"row\" dir=\"ltr\">\n<th class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" id=\"gzg1665703134326__d6308e20__entry__1\">Value</th>\n<th class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" id=\"gzg1665703134326__d6308e20__entry__2\">Meaning</th>\n</tr>\n</thead><tbody class=\"tbody\">\n<tr class=\"row\" dir=\"ltr\">\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" headers=\"gzg1665703134326__d6308e20__entry__1\">\n&gt;0\n</td>\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" headers=\"gzg1665703134326__d6308e20__entry__2\">The number of bytes copied into the\n                        buffer.</td>\n</tr>\n<tr class=\"row\" dir=\"ltr\">\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" headers=\"gzg1665703134326__d6308e20__entry__1\">0 </td>\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" headers=\"gzg1665703134326__d6308e20__entry__2\">An error occurred.</td>\n</tr>\n<tr class=\"row\" dir=\"ltr\">\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" headers=\"gzg1665703134326__d6308e20__entry__1\">\n&lt;0\n</td>\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" headers=\"gzg1665703134326__d6308e20__entry__2\">The negated number of bytes copied into the\n                        buffer. The negative status indicates that more data is available in the\n                        field, and that you should call <code class=\"ph codeph\">uggetc</code> to get additional\n                        data. </td>\n</tr>\n</tbody></table></div>\n</section>\n<section class=\"section\" id=\"gzg1665703134326__topic_d85982e1_d85983e1_d85984e1_d85985e1_d85986e1\"><h2 class=\"title sectiontitle\" id=\"d303651e164\">Use</h2>\n<p class=\"p\" id=\"gzg1665703134326__d5947e20\">Library:  <span class=\"ph filepath\">yrtl</span>\n</p>\n</section>\n<section class=\"section\" id=\"gzg1665703134326__topic_d85987e1_d85988e1_d85989e1_d85990e1_d85991e1\"><h2 class=\"title sectiontitle\" id=\"d303651e177\">Description</h2>\n<p class=\"p\" id=\"gzg1665703134326__p_d121079e1_d121080e1_d121081e1\"><code class=\"ph codeph\">uggetc</code> moves an additional chunk\n            of occurrence data into the specified buffer. This function should be called only after\n            a previous call to <code class=\"ph codeph\">ugget</code> or <code class=\"ph codeph\">uggetc</code> returned a negative\n            value, to indicate there is more data available.</p>\n<p class=\"p\" id=\"gzg1665703134326__p_d121082e1_d121083e1_d121084e1\">Parameters and return values are the same as for\n               <code class=\"ph codeph\">ugget</code>. So if <code class=\"ph codeph\">uggetc</code> also returns a negative status,\n            it must be called repeatedly until a positive status is returned.</p>\n</section>\n<section class=\"section\" id=\"gzg1665703134326__section_e3x_rt1_1wb\"><h2 class=\"title sectiontitle\" id=\"d303651e203\">Example: ugget and uggetc</h2>\n<p class=\"p\">The following example illustrates how to use <code class=\"ph codeph\">ugget</code> and\n               <code class=\"ph codeph\">uggetc</code> to get the data from the current occurrence into a buffer.\n            Because the size of the occurrence is unknown, we read fixed chunks and expand the\n            buffer as necessary. The choice of 100 as the size of the fixed chunks to read is\n            arbitrary.</p>\n<div class=\"zDocsCodeExplanationContainer\"><button aria-label=\"Explain this code\" class=\"zDocsAiActionsButton\" data-target=\"#zDocsCodeExplanationModal_uniface_104gzg1665703134326_html_1\" data-toggle=\"modal\" tabindex=\"0\" type=\"button\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-code-explanation\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-code-explanation\"></use></svg>Explain this code</button></div><div class=\"code-toolbar\"><pre class=\"pre codeblock language-plaintext\" data-explanation-rendered=\"true\" id=\"gzg1665703134326__codeblock_i3v_tt1_1wb\" tabindex=\"0\"><code class=\"language-plaintext\">#include &lt;h3gl.h&gt;\n#define CHUNKSIZE 100\n\nEXPORT void getoccurrence ()\n{\nchar* buf;\nint len;\nint totlen;\n\nbuf = malloc(CHUNKSIZE); /* Allocate the buffer */\n\nlen = ugget(NULL, buf, CHUNKSIZE);/* Get the first chunk of data */\ntotlen = abs(len); /* Set total length */\n\nwhile ( len &lt; 0 ) /* More to come */\n{\n/* Make room for next chunk */\nbuf = realloc(buf, totlen+CHUNKSIZE);\n/* Read next chunk */\nlen = uggetc(NULL, buf+totlen, CHUNKSIZE);\n/* Update total length */\ntotlen += abs(len);\n}\n\nbuf = realloc(buf, totlen+1); /* Make room for terminator */\nbuf[totlen] = 0; /* Add terminator */\n}</code></pre><div class=\"toolbar\"><div class=\"toolbar-item\"><button class=\"copy-to-clipboard-button\" data-copy-state=\"copy\" type=\"button\"><span>Copy</span></button></div></div></div>\n</section>\n</div>\n</article></main></article>\n</div></div><div class=\"contentPlaceholder\" style=\"height: 500px;\"><div class=\"contentContainer zDocsSideBoxes\"><div><h5 aria-level=\"5\" class=\"css-g931ng\">Related Links</h5><ul><li><a class=\"css-ettsdk\" href=\"/de-DE/bundle/uniface_104/page/cdt1665703134186.html\" stylesprops=\"[object Object]\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-related-link\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-related-link\"></use></svg>ugget</a><p>Move data from the current occurrence of the specified entity or current entity into a program buffer.</p></li></ul></div></div></div></div><div class=\"bottomFeedback\"><div aria-labelledby=\"bottomFeedbackText\" class=\"bottomFeedbackContent\" role=\"group\"><span class=\"bottomFeedbackText\" id=\"bottomFeedbackText\">Was this topic helpful?</span><div class=\"bottomFeedbackButtonGroup\"><a data-backdrop=\"static\" data-target=\"#feedbackModal_bottom_2528104\" data-toggle=\"modal\" href=\"#\" role=\"button\" type=\"button\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-thumbs-up\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-thumbs-up\"></use></svg><span>Like</span></a><a data-backdrop=\"static\" data-target=\"#feedbackModal_bottom_2528104\" data-toggle=\"modal\" href=\"#\" role=\"button\" type=\"button\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-thumbs-down\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-thumbs-down\"></use></svg><span>Dislike</span></a></div></div></div><div style=\"position: fixed; bottom: 170px; right: 70px; cursor: pointer; transition-duration: 0.2s; transition-timing-function: linear; transition-delay: 0s; z-index: 3; opacity: 0; visibility: hidden; transition-property: opacity, visibility;\"><button aria-label=\"Scroll to top\" class=\"zDocsScrollTopBtn\" data-tooltip-content=\"Scroll to top\" data-tooltip-id=\"zDocsBackToTopToolTip\" id=\"zDocsScrollToTop\" type=\"button\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-next\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-next\"></use></svg></button></div></body></html>", "text": "uggetc Add to My Topics Add selected topic and subtopics Add Topic & Subtopics with topic head Add entire publication Watch Download PDF Save selected topic Save selected topic and subtopics Save entire publication Share Email Link Copy Link Feedback Last Updated Dez 30, 2022 Summarize Uniface 10.4 Move additional data from the current occurrence of the specified entity or current entity into a program buffer. Explain this code short uggetc (unsigned char* entity, unsigned char* buffer, short max); Copy Parameters entity The name of the entity whose data you want to get. A value of NULL denotes the current entity. buffer (Output) The buffer containing the data. max The maximum number of bytes that should be moved. This should not exceed the size of the buffer. Return Values Table 1. Values returned by ugget and uggetc Value Meaning >0 The number of bytes copied into the buffer. 0 An error occurred. <0 The negated number of bytes copied into the buffer. The negative status indicates that more data is available in the field, and that you should call uggetc to get additional data. Use Library: yrtl Description uggetc moves an additional chunk of occurrence data into the specified buffer. This function should be called only after a previous call to ugget or uggetc returned a negative value, to indicate there is more data available. Parameters and return values are the same as for ugget . So if uggetc also returns a negative status, it must be called repeatedly until a positive status is returned. Example: ugget and uggetc The following example illustrates how to use ugget and uggetc to get the data from the current occurrence into a buffer. Because the size of the occurrence is unknown, we read fixed chunks and expand the buffer as necessary. The choice of 100 as the size of the fixed chunks to read is arbitrary. Explain this code #include <h3gl.h> #define CHUNKSIZE 100 EXPORT void getoccurrence () { char* buf; int len; int totlen; buf = malloc(CHUNKSIZE); /* Allocate the buffer */ len = ugget(NULL, buf, CHUNKSIZE);/* Get the first chunk of data */ totlen = abs(len); /* Set total length */ while ( len < 0 ) /* More to come */ { /* Make room for next chunk */ buf = realloc(buf, totlen+CHUNKSIZE); /* Read next chunk */ len = uggetc(NULL, buf+totlen, CHUNKSIZE); /* Update total length */ totlen += abs(len); } buf = realloc(buf, totlen+1); /* Make room for terminator */ buf[totlen] = 0; /* Add terminator */ } Copy Related Links ugget Move data from the current occurrence of the specified entity or current entity into a program buffer. Was this topic helpful? Like Dislike"}